# Agent Does Everything Possible

- Do every step that Cursor can do (edit files, run terminal commands, commit, push, run scripts, etc.). Do not give the user instructions to do those steps themselves.
- Only ask the user to do something when (1) the agent genuinely cannot do it (e.g. buy a domain in a browser, enter a password, approve a payment, sign in to a third-party UI), or (2) having the agent do it would incur usage/cost you want to avoid—in that case you may hand off that one step to the user.
- Never ask the user to do something just because it's "easier" to describe; do it yourself unless it's impossible for the agent or you're avoiding agent usage/cost.
- Prefer: run the command, make the edit, push the change. Not: "Run this in your terminal" or "Add this to your env."
- If a task requires the user (e.g. paste an API key, click Deploy in Vercel UI), do all agent-doable steps first, then one short instruction for the single user step.
